  <mods:abstract>Description:&#xA0;(1 extra print; also close-up of man by the window, #4287) #4288 From: Old Men's Toy Shop Album Unknown Photographer In "Last Year's Work and This Year's Challenge"; 76th Annual Report of AICP (1918-1919), page 12 bottom. Caption: Crawford Work Shops where many old, old men and women whom industry in general doesn't want "to be bothered with" are given a chance to do two things - (l) make a living;(2) make all sorts of quaint things for young, young children. Yes, and a third thing, to keep out of the dreaded almshouse.</mods:abstract>
